-- Canadian Pacific Removes Train Cars from Calgary Bridge
-- B y   G e r r i t   D e   V y n c k
-- 2013-06-28T12:10:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-28/canadian-pacific-removes-train-cars-from-calgary-bridge.html
Canadian Pacific Railway Ltd. pulled
six derailed train cars off a buckling bridge in Calgary.  The cars were drained of petroleum diluent,  Ed Greenberg , a
company spokesman, said in an e-mailed statement today. Five of
the cars were carrying the product used to dilute heavy oil.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gerrit De Vynck in Toronto at 
 gdevynck@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
